    "question": "d/dx [log⁡(4x<sup>3</sup> - 2x) ] is equal to",
    "option": {
      "a": "(12x−2)/4x<sup>2</sup>",
      "b": "(43x<sup>2</sup>−2x)/7x",
      "c": "(4x<sup>2</sup>−2)/7x+6",
      "d": "(12x<sup>2</sup>−2)/4x<sup>3</sup>−2x",
      "e": null
    },
    "section": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>d</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n  <mi>log</mi>\n  <mo>&#x2061;<!-- ⁡ --></mo>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <msup>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msup>\n  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- − --></mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n</math>",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "d",
    "solution": "d/dx [log(4x<sup>3</sup> - 2x) ]   ... (1)\n\nLet u = 4x<sup>3</sup - 2x.\n\nd/dx(log(4x<sup>3</sup> − 2x)) = (d/du)(du/dx)\nd/du(logu) = 1/u\ndu/dx = 12x<sup>2</sup> − 2\n∴d/dx[log(4x<sup>3</sup> − 2x) ]= (12x<sup>2</sup> − 2)/u\n= (12x<sup>2</sup> − 2)/(4x<sup>3</sup> − 2x)",
    "examtype": "utme",
    "examyear": "2019"
  },
